  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The creation of ACBF was in response to the severity of Africa&#xBF;s capacity needs, and the challenge of investing in indigenous human capital and institutions in sub-Saharan Africa. ACBF was therefore designed to serve as a coordinating mechanism for donor support to capacity building on the Continent, through the pooling of resources and a common governance and reporting system. 

The targets set out in the organization&apos;s strategic plan within the six areas of focus will build capacity among civil servants in public institutions in order to promote the formulation and implementation of economic and social reforms, poverty reduction strategies and good governance in an open and transparent dialogue with civil society and the private sector. Also the capacities of the AU and the regional economic institutions is targeted to promote economic integration and adaptation to globalization.</narrative>
  </description>
